<Content_wSideColumn ID="x28874" Name="Spori Summit" Layout="byuidefault.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Spori Summit</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Information regarding the annual BYU-Idaho Faculty Spori Summit.</Abstract><xPower Type="GroupStart" GroupStart="" Name="SideColumn" label="L/R Column" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded="false"><MoveLeft type="boolean" label="Toggle column right or left (right is default)" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</MoveLeft><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="ImageComponent" label="Image Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="LeftColumnImageComponent" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="TextComponent" label="Text Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="ColumnTextComponent" Expanded="false"/><fbookTop type="boolean" label="Put facebook at top of page" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</fbookTop><fbookStatus type="string" label="Facebook ID#" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"></fbookStatus><fbookToken type="string" label="Access_Token" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"></fbookToken><fbookDisplayed type="string" label="Number of facebook messages to display" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">1</fbookDisplayed></xPower><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p>The Spori Summit is patterned after the Great Teacher's Seminar model and is designed to allow open discussion about teaching challenges and successes with colleagues from across all disciplines.&nbsp;<br /><br />This overnight retreat is held at the Sky Mountain Ranch west of Victor, ID every fall. It is a faculty sponsored retreat run by the&nbsp;<a href="x23098.xml">Best Practices Committee</a>. The retreat allows professors from various backgrounds the opportunity to share ideas about instruction in a relaxed atmosphere. It is also an opportunity to develop lasting friendships with colleagues from across campus that care deeply about learning the art of teaching.<br /><br />The 2014 summit will be held October 2-3, and will be limited to 25 faculty.&nbsp; To reserve your place please RSVP to InstructionalDevelopment@byui.edu.</p>
